                .competitive-audit__analysis
                    .analysis
                        %hr.if-divider
                        .columns.is-multiline
                            .column.is-4-desktop.is-6-tablet
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.navy
                                            %p Strong Brand Presence
                                        %p.card-title FirstBank Puerto Rico
                                        %p.card-subtitle Direct Competitor
                                        %p.card-text
                                            Polished design with solid brand credibility and a well-organized product suite. The personal loan page leads with rates and benefits clearly, and the blog and "Watch and Learn" video section show investment in financial education. However, the loan product lives inside a large navigation ecosystem, and the application flow redirects to a third-party portal, creating a noticeable break in the experience.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            The loan journey loses continuity at the most critical moment. Island Finance can win by keeping the user in one seamless, focused flow.
                            .column.is-4-desktop.is-6-tablet
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.beige
                                            %p Educational Content Leader
                                        %p.card-title Oriental Bank
                                        %p.card-subtitle Direct Competitor
                                        %p.card-text
                                            One of the few local banks investing in financial literacy, with educational resources and a blog aimed at consumers of all ages. However, the site design is visually dated, with heavy navigation, image-based UI elements, and a personal loan page buried deep inside a broad product ecosystem. The experience feels institutional, not borrower-focused.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Clean navigation and a visible calculator are table stakes. Financial literacy content is the gap across the board.
                            .column.is-4-desktop.is-6-tablet
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.blue
                                            %p Market Leader
                                        %p.card-title Banco Popular PR
                                        %p.card-subtitle Direct Competitor
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The strongest digital experience among local competitors. Soft-pull prequalification, a loan calculator surfaced directly in the navigation, and same-day disbursement make the experience fast and transparent. As the island's largest bank, though, the experience is built for breadth, and the fine print is dense.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Large institutions sacrifice product-level clarity for ecosystem breadth. Island Finance can win on single-product focus and simplicity.    
                            .column.is-4-desktop.is-6-tablet
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.orange
                                            %p Shared Audience
                                        %p.card-title Kiwi Credito
                                        %p.card-subtitle Direct Competitor
                                        %p.card-text
                                            Targets the same underserved borrowers, with a clean, mobile-first flow and a credit builder product that appeals to first-time borrowers. With no loan calculator, financial education or physical presence, it doesn't do much to earn the borrower's trust. The site relies entirely on vague customer reviews. The design is generic and the loan ceiling is low.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Has the audience and the flow but not the depth. Island Finance has higher loan amounts, 49 branches, and a founding mission that Kiwi can't replicate.
                            .column.is-4-desktop.is-6-tablet
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.green
                                            %p Digital Benchmark
                                        %p.card-title LendingClub
                                        %p.card-subtitle Indirect — US digital lending
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The benchmark for digital-first personal lending. Transparent rate display from the first page, an intuitive loan calculator, clear APR communication, and a step-by-step application flow that reduces anxiety at every stage.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Clearly communicates value before the application starts. It proves that surfacing rate ranges, soft-pull checks, and clear product info early removes hesitation.
                            .column.is-4-desktop.is-6-tablet
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.green
                                            %p Hybrid Model Benchmark
                                        %p.card-title OneMain Financial
                                        %p.card-subtitle Indirect — US digital lending
                                        %p.card-text
                                            One of the few lenders combining a digital flow with physical branches. No minimum credit score, same-day funding, and a resource center with calculators and education content. The weak point is transparency: prequalification hides APR behind a hard credit pull, adding friction at the worst moment.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Hiding APR behind a hard credit pull creates hesitation. Clear rate ranges and terms should be displayed before the borrower commits to anything.
        .case-study__user-interviews
            .anchor#interviews
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow User Interviews
                        %h3 Understanding Users
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p To understand how Island Finance customers experience the service, user feedback and reviews were analyzed for recurring themes. Four patterns emerged that directly shaped the design direction.
                        .case-study__interview-quotes
                            .columns.is-multiline.is-variable.is-3-desktop
                                .column.is-6
                                    .case-study-quote.red
                                        .case-study__quote-label.c1
                                            %p Trust
                                        %p "They should invest to improve the Banking Network Architecture with a good IT team to make it convenient enough for the customer. I genuinely do not recommend this or any other bank that does not have good IT service."
                                .column.is-6
                                    .case-study-quote.blue
                                        .case-study__quote-label.c2
                                            %p Hidden Costs
                                        %p "I'm still paying a loan that I took out for 2,500, I ended up paying 5,000. The APR is 32%. Something that has to be taken into account, I didn't know because it was my first time. Don't borrow here."
                                .column.is-6
                                    .case-study-quote.orange
                                        .case-study__quote-label.c3
                                            %p Clarity
                                        %p "They do not explain the difference between changing a debit date vs changing the loan payment date, which turns out to be two completely different things. It took 3 calls for someone to satisfactorily guide me."
                                .column.is-6
                                    .case-study-quote.navy
                                        .case-study__quote-label.c4
                                            %p Digital Management
                                        %p "Phantom charges, and they want to charge surcharges for cashier errors. The cashier swiped the card for .10 cents less and they want to charge me $10 more for allegedly not having paid on time."
                        .case-study__interview-takeaways
                            %ul
                                %li
                                    %span Digital reliability signals institutional competence.
                                    Outdated IT infrastructure signals that the institution itself is unreliable. A modern, fast, well-functioning site directly changes how users perceive the company's credibility.
                                %li
                                    %span Trust and transparency are the core problem. 
                                    Users feel misled about costs, fees, and how the product works. The redesign prioritizes upfront APR communication, clear fee disclosure, and plain-language explanations at every step.
                                %li
                                    %span Financial literacy gaps cause real harm.
                                    Users do not understand product features, payment options, or how interest accrues. Educational content and plain-language definitions reduce confusion and prevent the negative experiences users described.
                                %li
                                    %span Digital self-service is a baseline expectation.
                                    Users want to manage payments, check balances, and resolve issues without calling a branch.
        .case-study__problem-statement
            .anchor#problem
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Challenges
                        %h3 Problem Statement
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p The necessity to upgrade Island Finance's banking website became clear after analyzing competitors and gathering user feedback. With an increasing demand for digital services among clients, this enhancement is crucial for the company's future growth.
                        %p The current website lacked essential features and made it difficult for users to perform tasks like calculating loan payments, making online payments, and accessing loan information. This led to confusion regarding their financial situations. Additionally, the outdated design reinforced the perception of Island Finance as a traditional and complicated company, which did not align with the company's brand image and value proposition.
        .case-study__main-concerns
            .anchor#concerns
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Main Concerns
                        %h3 Constraints and Considerations
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        .main-concerns__concerns-wrapper
                            %p Redesigning the Island Finance experience meant balancing real user frustrations with internal constraints that shaped what was possible. Together, these informed every design decision.
                            .columns.is-multiline.is-variable.is-8-desktop
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
                                            %p 💻
                                        %h4 Trust & Credibility
                                        %p An outdated website and unreliable IT services raised red flags for clients, signaling a lack of professionalism. Every screen had to counter that through clean layouts, upfront fee explanations, and clear action feedback that rebuilt confidence in the platform.
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
                                            %p 📚
                                        %h4 Financial Literacy
                                        %p Low financial literacy makes the loan process confusing and overwhelming. Rather than just presenting information, we designed the experience to guide and teach using plain copy and step-by-step flows to reduce overwhelm and encourage more responsible borrowing.
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
                                            %p 🤝
                                        %h4 Transparency
                                        %p Fear of hidden fees and unclear terms slows down decision-making and drives potential borrowers elsewhere. We made disclosures and loan terms a natural part of the flow, keeping things clear and compliant without feeling cold or bureaucratic.
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
                                            %p 📱
                                        %h4 Digital Loan Management
                                        %p Without the ability to manage loans digitally, the experience feels outdated and frustrating. Legacy infrastructure limited how far we could go, so we prioritized simple, scalable solutions that gave customers real convenience without requiring deep backend overhauls.
        .case-study__project-goals
            .anchor#goals
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Objectives
                        %h3 Revewing Project Goals
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p Island Finance's business goals around conversion and digital adoption were only achievable if the site actually worked for the people visiting it. The goal was to identify where those interests converged and design toward that intersection.
                        .project-goals__graph
                            .columns
                                .column
                                    .graph__business-title
                                        %p Business goals
                                .column
                                    .graph__mutual-title
                                        %p Project goals
                                .column
                                    .graph__user-title
                                        %p User goals
                            .columns.is-vcentered.graph-columns
                                .column
                                    .graph__business-goals
                                        %ul
                                            %li Increase conversions
                                            %li Boost repeat loans
                                            %li Grow digital adoption
                                            %li Build brand credibility
                                            %li Expand digital channels
                                .column
                                    .graph__mutual-goals
                                        %ul
                                            %li Trust and transparency
                                            %li Clear loan terms
                                            %li Digital self-service
                                            %li Educated borrowers
                                .column
                                    .graph__user-goals
                                        %ul
                                            %li Apply with confidence
                                            %li Understand total cost
                                            %li Manage loans online
                                            %li No hidden surprises
                                            %li Fast decisions
        .case-study__features
            .anchor#features
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %h5 Features
                        %h3 Transforming Needs into Features
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p
                            Based on the user needs identified during the empathizing phase, we decided to focus on a few key features to enhance customer's experience.
                .columns.is-multiline.is-variable.is-3-desktop
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature
                            %h4.green Loan Calculator
                            %h3 Explore options before committing
                            %p Helps users explore their options risk free. It clearly presents loan details, prevents surprises about future charges, and builds trust.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature
                            %h4.blue Online Application
                            %h3 Apply anytime, from any device
                            %p Makes it easy for users to apply anytime, from any device. It guides them through each step with clear instructions and built-in validation to reduce errors and confusion.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature
                            %h4.orange Online Payments
                            %h3 Manage loans without a branch visit
                            %p Gives users a simple and secure way to manage their loans. It reduces the need for branch visits, saves time, and encourages on-time payments through clear guidance and easy access from any device.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature
                            %h4.navy Loan Dashboard
                            %h3 Stay informed and in control
                            %p Gives users a clear overview of their account in one place. They can track balances, upcoming payments, and loan details at a glance. It simplifies management, builds confidence, and helps users stay informed and in control of their finances.
        .case-study__user-flows
            .anchor#flows
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow User Flows
                        %h3 Identifying how users complete tasks
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p To truly support users, we needed to understand how they actually got things done, how they navigate, what they expect, and where they might hesitate. Mapping their steps helped us design flows that feel natural, supportive, and frustration-free.
                        %h4 Applying for a loan through nav bar button:
                        = image_tag "https://nicolada-website.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Request-a-loan-1.png", :class => "user-flows__img", :loading => 'lazy'
        .case-studies__navigation-wrapper.if-web
                        %h4 Applying for a loan through the calculator:
                        = image_tag "https://nicolada-website.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Request-a-loan-2.png", :class => "user-flows__img", :loading => 'lazy'
        .case-studies__navigation-wrapper.if-web
                        %h4 Making a payment:
                        = image_tag "https://nicolada-website.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Make-a-payment.png", :class => "user-flows__img", :loading => 'lazy'
        .case-studies__navigation-wrapper.if-web
